This paper involves the use of deep learning and convolutional neural networks for predicting stress fields in structures, which falls under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE). The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of prediction errors and the comparison of different architectures, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the application of these techniques to structural design and topology optimization suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SI).
